AUDIO: 'our own innovations, which today cannot be supported by externals. Our viewer, there are because there are two use cases, you know. There are the use case where someone is going to just retrieve our format and not modify it and just serve it on the web, which is bulk of'

[09:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what 3D commerce is for. 3D commerce, what they want, they want to scan something and they want to be able to push that scan onto the web and be able to use that as imagery to sell their product. So, they don\'t want to modify it. They just want something that works'

[10:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fast, that is high fidelity. And in this case, our viewer makes total sense because then we offer the the workflow for from end to end with a level of quality that we master throughout. Then, there\'s the use case where people want to modify the splat they get. And that'

